faqs:
  - q: "How does laminate compare to hardwood?"
    a: "Laminate offers the look of hardwood at a significantly lower price point. While it can't be refinished like real wood, modern laminate is highly scratch-resistant and durable. It's an excellent choice for budget-conscious homeowners who want beautiful floors without the hardwood price tag."
  - q: "Is laminate flooring waterproof?"
    a: "Traditional laminate is water-resistant but not waterproof — standing water can cause damage. For wet areas like bathrooms and kitchens, we recommend LVP instead. However, newer water-resistant laminate products perform well in areas with occasional moisture like living rooms and bedrooms."
  - q: "How long does laminate installation take?"
    a: "Laminate installs quickly because it's a floating floor system — planks click together without glue or nails. Most rooms can be completed in a single day. A whole-home laminate project typically takes 2-3 days."
  - q: "Can laminate be installed in a basement?"
    a: "Yes, with the right product and preparation. We use moisture-resistant laminate with a proper vapor barrier for basement installations. Ake will test your basement slab for moisture levels during the estimate to ensure the right approach."
