<h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);font-weight:600;color:var(--text-primary);margin-top:var(--space-2xl);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">What Affects Laminate Installation Cost?</h3>
<p style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Laminate is one of the most budget-friendly flooring options. Here's what influences pricing:</p>
<ul style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:2;padding-left:var(--space-lg);">
  <li><strong>Product grade</strong> — Entry-level vs. premium laminate with thicker cores and better textures</li>
  <li><strong>Underlayment</strong> — Some products include attached pad; others need separate underlayment</li>
  <li><strong>Subfloor condition</strong> — Leveling or moisture barriers may be needed, especially in basements</li>
  <li><strong>Old flooring removal</strong> — Removing existing carpet, tile, or vinyl adds to the project</li>
  <li><strong>Room layout</strong> — Complex room shapes with many cuts and transitions require more labor</li>
</ul>
<p style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;margin-top:var(--space-md);">Laminate is often the most affordable path to beautiful floors. <a href="/contact/" style="color:var(--brand-primary);font-weight:600;">Get your free estimate</a> and Ake will walk you through options for every budget.</p>
